                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre but careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, vivid red.</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS11077Zadengel">Za-Dǝngǝl</persName> is
                        mentioned as the scribe in the colophon (he also copied Mss. QSM-005,
                        MY-019, AQG-002, AGM-001).<date>FIrst half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይብል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>የዲ፡ (sic) for ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ካ፡ for ካህን፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of Text I; directives to the
                           ministers and their abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD; On the incipit page of Text I (fols.
                           3r), a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
